<HEADLINE>
<P>
DIGEST /LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: WATER RATES TO RISE 12% IN NOVEMBER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Palmdale Water District has approved its first rate increase in nearly two 
years, with most of the district's 17,000 customers expected to pay about 12% 
more for water starting in November. 
</P>
<P>
The five-member board of directors of the public water district, which serves 
the east side of Palmdale and surrounding unincorporated areas, adopted the 
increase Tuesday night in an attempt to cover a forecast deficit of about 
$800,000 for the current calendar year. 
</P>
<P>
The amount of increase varies by type of user. But district officials said a 
typical residential customer now paying about $31 a month to use about 30,000 
gallons would now pay about $35 a month. The district last increased rates in 
February, 1989. 
</P>
</TEXT>
