<HEADLINE>
<P>
HONOR STUDENT CHARGED WITH STABBING TEACHER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
CORAL SPRINGS, Fla. 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Police charged a 16-year-old honor student with attempted homicide after he 
allegedly stabbed his physics teacher with a kitchen knife in an argument over 
a test grade. David Pologruto, 41, a teacher at Taravella High School, was 
listed as stable at a medical center after the assault Tuesday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
