<P>
Sears, Roebuck &amp; Co.: The nation's largest retailer said its third-quarter 
profit fell 30% from a year ago to $179.2 million despite a 5.9% revenue 
increase to $13.96 billion. Sears cited sharply lower gains from sales of 
property in the Coldwell Banker Real Estate Group, reflecting the soft 
residential real estate market. Earnings from the Sears Merchandise and Dean 
Witter Financial Services groups improved while Allstate Insurance Group's 
earnings declined, the Chicago-based company said. 
