<HEADLINE>
<P>
METRO DIGEST / LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: SPORTS GRANTS AWARDED BY 1984 OLYMPICS FUND 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The foundation that distributes 1984 Olympic surplus funds to Southern 
California youth sports projects announced in Los Angeles another $373,160 in 
grants, bringing to more than $18 million the grants made in the last five 
years. 
</P>
<P>
The largest of the 20 new Amateur Athletic Foundation grants -- $64,800 -- went 
to the Phoenix Houses of California for a sports program for youths 13 to 18 
enrolled in drug rehabilitation. A $50,200 grant went to the Crittenton Center 
in Los Angeles to establish a sports program for women in their teens who have 
been placed in the center. 
</P>
</TEXT>
