<HEADLINE>
<P>
METRO DIGEST / LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: MORE RAPES CHARGED IN 'MESSENGER OF LORD' 
CASE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A 28-year-old graduate student who police believe is the so-called "Messenger 
of the Lord" rapist has been charged with six additional counts of sexual 
assault involving two more victims. 
</P>
<P>
Joseph Brian Socha had been charged earlier this month with a string of attacks 
in Long Beach and San Pedro that occurred between August and September. Socha 
now faces a total of 24 counts of robbery, kidnaping and sexual assault 
involving six women. His arraignment is set for Wednesday in Long Beach. 
</P>
<P>
The new charges, filed last week, involve attacks that occurred in August 
before the previously reported attacks. One of the victims was assaulted in 
Inglewood, the other in Long Beach. 
</P>
</TEXT>
