435 words 
</P>
</LENGTH>
<HEADLINE>
<P>
BEST BITES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The following are capsule reviews of some of the better restaurants recently 
visited by our critics: 
</P>
<P>
Waterfront dining is alive in -- of all places -- inland Ventura County, at New 
Orleans West. On the Westlake shore, NOW does best with its appetizers, such as 
the tangy chicken fingers, and the more elaborate Seafood Casa Dorata is 
certainly full of seafood. At either the patio or the bar, it's a lovely 
environment. New Orleans West, 32131 Lindero Canyon Blvd., Westlake Village, 
(818) 707-9378. Monday through Saturday 11:30 a.m. to 10 p.m. Sunday 11 a.m. to 
10 p.m. Sunday brunch. Full bar, credit cards accepted. Meal for two, food 
only, $20 to $50. 
</P>
<P>
The 24-page menu at Jack's Restaurant and Deli offers everything from Mexican 
and American to vegetarian and deli food. The beers come in 136 varieties. Try 
the sweet, tangy baby-back pork ribs or the Mexican dishes, which are 
particularly good. Jack's is in Westlake Plaza Shopping Center, Westlake 
Village; 495-8181. Open every day for breakfast, lunch and dinner. Monday 
through Thursday 7 a.m. to midnight; Friday 7 a.m. to 1:30 a.m.; Saturday 7:30 
a.m. to 1:30 a.m.; Sunday 7:30 a.m. to 11:30 p.m. Dinner for two, food only, 
$19 to $52. 
</P>
<P>
You can go to Santa Barbara's crown jewel, the Four Seasons Biltmore Hotel, for 
more than just the atmosphere or the Sunday brunch buffet. The kitchen is now 
among the best in town, turning out wonderful dishes from lobster sausages to a 
bittersweet chocolate souffle. Better at dinner than at lunch. Either the 
indoor La Marina or the sparkling outdoor Patio makes for romantic dining. The 
Four Seasons Biltmore is at 1260 Channel Drive, Santa Barbara; 969-2261. 
Serving in the Patio weekdays 6:30 a.m. to 10 p.m., weekends 6:30 a.m. to 11 
p.m. Serving in La Marina weekdays 6 to 10 p.m., weekends 6 to 11 p.m. Lunch 
for two, food only, $30 to $48. Dinner for two, food only, $50 to $70. 
</P>
<P>
The pub at Victoria Pub and Restaurant is a lively gathering place for English 
expatriates and pub lovers alike. It stays open until everyone goes home, and 
the dart games never stop. The more subdued restaurant serves an English menu, 
complete with steak and kidney pie, fish and chips and Cornish pasties. The 
soups, which are changed every day, are excellent, as is the lamb steak. The 
crumble of the day with hot fruit, sweet crumble and cream is particularly 
good. Victoria Pub and Restaurant is at 1413F S. Victoria Ave., Ventura; 
650-0060. Lunch is served every day from 11 a.m. to 3 p.m. Dinner is served 
from 5 to 9:30 p.m., and the pub is open until 2 a.m. Dinner for two, food 
only, $25 to $60. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<GRAPHIC>
<P>
Photo, dining room 
</P>
</GRAPHIC>
<TYPE>
<P>
Restaurant Review 
</P>
</TYPE>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA102590-0077 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 297501 </DOCID>
<DATE>
