<HEADLINE>
<P>
PREP ROUNDUP; 
</P>
<P>
EDISON GOALIE STANTON SHUTS OUT OCEAN VIEW IN WATER POLO 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Jason Stanton had 12 saves to lead Edison to a 15-0 victory over Ocean View in 
a Sunset League water polo game at Golden West College Wednesday. 
</P>
<P>
Stanton, a sophomore, accomplished a feat that is as rare in water polo as a 
no-hitter is in baseball. 
</P>
<P>
The victory gave Edison, 15-7 and 5-0 in league, the Sunset League title. Brian 
Melstrom scored four goals for Edison. 
</P>
<P>
In Sea View League water polo: 
</P>
<P>
Corona del Mar 12, Tustin 4 -- Ryan Weir and Ted Simpkins each had three goals 
and Robbie Pike had nine saves for host Corona del Mar (20-1). 
</P>
<P>
In Orange League water polo: 
</P>
<P>
Brea-Olinda 17, Savanna 2 -- Scott Estrada and Kyle Kilpatrick each scored 
three goals and Bryan Noyes, Steve Krebs and Jason Bird each scored two to lead 
Brea-Olinda (18-4, 7-0). Matt Priess had 15 saves, and the Brea-Olinda goalie 
scored his seventh goal of the season. 
</P>
<P>
In Pacific Coast League girls' volleyball: 
</P>
<P>
Laguna Beach 3, Laguna Hills 0 -- Tori Scott, a junior middle blocker, had 
seven kills to lead Laguna Beach (14-4, 7-0) to a 15-4, 15-1, 15-3 sweep of 
host Laguna Hills. Senior setter Kealy Clarke had 29 assists and four aces for 
Laguna Beach. 
</P>
<P>
Trabuco Hills 3, Century 0: Erin Woffinden had 11 aces to lead visiting Trabuco 
Hills (3-7, 3-4). 
</P>
<P>
In Olympic League girls' tennis: 
</P>
<P>
Connelly 11, Valley Christian 7 -- Lisa Kang and Ann Johnston swept, 6-4, 6-0, 
6-2, to lead host Connelly (8-7, 6-2). 
</P>
<P>
In Empire League girls' tennis: 
</P>
<P>
Esperanza 13, Cypress 5 -- Emily Haas swept for Cypress. 
</P>
</TEXT>
