<HEADLINE>
<P>
MORNING REPORT: PEOPLEWATCH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By BETH KLEID, Arts and entertainment reports from The Times, national and 
international news services and the nation's press. 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Wyeth at the White House: Artist Andrew Wyeth, 73, said it was "really wild" to 
receive a congressional gold medal from President Bush. 
</P>
<P>
At a White House ceremony Wednesday marking the first such presentation to an 
artist, Bush said, "As the legislative citation reads: We act today in 
recognition of Andrew Wyeth's outstanding and invaluable contributions to 
American art and culture. He is, of course, one of America's foremost artists." 
The medal was patterned after a portrait of Wyeth by his son Jamie. BETH KLEID 
</P>
</TEXT>
