<HEADLINE>
<P>
PEOPLE IN THE NEWS: PASADENA DIRECTOR MAKES IT OFFICIAL, GETS MARRIED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Pasadena City Director Chris Holden took a break from city politics to get 
married Saturday in Pasadena's Westminster Presbyterian Church. 
</P>
<P>
Before more than 400 well-wishers, Holden married Michelle Watkins, a loan 
officer with Mortgage Link in Ontario. 
</P>
<P>
The reception was in Pasadena's Central Library on Walnut Street. It was the 
first wedding reception at the newly renovated library, which has begun renting 
out its space to raise money. 
</P>
<P>
The new bride and Holden, son of Los Angeles City Councilman Nate Holden, are 
vacationing in Europe for two weeks. 
</P>
<P>
* L. Norman Howe, founder and chief executive officer of F &amp; P Inc., a 
Pasadena marketing company, has been named a regional winner of the 1990 
"Chivas Regal Extrapreneur Awards." 
</P>
<P>
Howe received the award for raising more than $11 million in the last 11 years 
for the City of Hope medical treatment center in Duarte by developing grocery 
store "Coupons of Hope." Food companies pay for advertising on the coupons, and 
that money goes to the City of Hope. 
</P>
<P>
The 16 regional awards recognize imaginative public service by those in 
business. Six winners will be named from among the regional winners at a 
ceremony in New York in early November. 
</P>
<P>
Items for People in the News may be mailed to 1333 Mayflower Ave., Suite 200, 
Monrovia, 91016. 
</P>
