<HEADLINE>
<P>
SCHOOL NEWS: PASADENA ELKS DONATE $500 FOR DRUG BANNERS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Pasadena Elks Lodge No. 672 has donated $500 to buy 20 anti-drug banners for 
the Pasadena Unified School District in honor of Red Ribbon Week. 
</P>
<P>
Each elementary school in the district will get an 8-by-4-foot banner with the 
slogan, "Line up to sign up for a drug free decade." Posters will be provided 
where pupils, teachers, parents and staff can sign their names under the 
banner. 
</P>
<P>
Red Ribbon Week is a nationwide anti-drug campaign to urge students to lead 
healthy, drug-free lives. 
</P>
