<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY NEWSWATCH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Chris Woodyard and Len Hall 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HAPPY BIRTHDAY: Seal Beach, celebrating its 75th anniversary this weekend, was 
not always the upscale, upstanding town it is now. . . . In the Roaring '20s, 
it attracted hordes of actors for Cecil B. DeMille's "Ten Commandments" (look 
for oil wells behind the pursuing Egyptians), and drew carnival crowds to watch 
aviators loop the loop (and occasionally crash). . . . With prostitution and 
gambling, it was also the closest thing to a Sin City the county ever had. 
Chris Woodyard and Len Hall 
</P>
</TEXT>
