<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: LAGUNA HILLS; 
</P>
<P>
GOODS SOUGHT FOR GULF CARE PACKAGE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
While American military men and women linger in Middle East deserts, Joy 
Hallamore doesn't want them to be bored. 
</P>
<P>
So the Laguna Hills resident is organizing a drive to collect new and used 
recreational goods such as games, cards, magazines, books, balls, puzzles and 
audio cassettes, to help relieve the tedium in the Persian Gulf. 
</P>
<P>
"Operation Care Package" will be collecting donated goods from 10 a.m. to 7 
p.m. Saturday in front of the Laguna Hills Target Store at La Paz Road and 
Pacific Park Drive. 
</P>
<P>
"I just wanted to do something," said Hallamore, whose cousin left recently for 
Saudi Arabia. She decided on the collection drive after hearing a radio 
announcement asking residents to send such items. And she figured that people 
were more likely to donate such goods if someone else -- such as her 
organization -- handles the task of shipping the items. 
</P>
<P>
For more information, call (714) 362-1175. 
</P>
</TEXT>
