<HEADLINE>
<P>
WESTSIDE DIGEST: SANTA MONICA; 
</P>
<P>
CAMP SCHOLARSHIPS FUNDED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
National Medical Enterprises Inc., one of the nation's largest health care 
companies, has donated $3,000 to the Malibu Youth Foundation for summer sports 
camp scholarships next year. 
</P>
<P>
Craig Dummit, president of the foundation, said the grant will allow 10 
children to attend the camp. 
</P>
