<HEADLINE>
<P>
FOR THE RECORD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Consultants -- A new rule approved by the Pasadena Board of Directors on 
environmental impact reports for proposed developments was reported incorrectly 
Sunday. Rather than having developers choose consultants from a city list, the 
new rule requires the city to contract directly with the consultants, with the 
developer reimbursing the city. 
</P>
</TEXT>
