<HEADLINE>
<P>
STATE; 
</P>
<P>
LOTTO PRIZE NEARING $20 MILLION 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
SACRAMENTO 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
No one won the $14.9-million jackpot in the midweek Lotto 6/53 drawing, but 
four players won $152,794 each by picking five of the six numbers and the bonus 
number, state lottery officials said today. 
</P>
<P>
The winners in the five-of-six-plus-bonus category bought their tickets in 
Meadow Vista, Westminster, Palm Desert and Chino, officials said. 
</P>
<P>
Ticket sales totaled $11.1 million. Saturday's jackpot was estimated at $20 
million. 
</P>
</TEXT>
