<P>
JET LOSES WHEEL, LANDS SAFELY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
ORLANDO, Fla. 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A Continental Airlines jetliner with 85 people aboard made a safe emergency 
landing here today after losing one of a pair of landing gear wheels on 
takeoff, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
Flight 358 had left Ft. 
</P>
<P>
Myers on Florida's Gulf Coast en route to Newark, N.J., and Boston when the 
wheel detached, said Arlene Salac of the Federal Aviation Administration in 
Atlanta. 
</P>
<P>
"The right outer main gear wheel came off of the aircraft," she said. "There 
are two wheels on each gear, but one of them is what came off." 
</P>
<P>
The plane was diverted to Orlando International Airport and circled before 
landing at 1:36 p.m., said airport spokeswoman Linda Desrosiers. It landed 
without incident and the passengers were taken off by bus. 
</P>
