SHORT TAKES; 
</P>
<P>
WAYLON FINALLY MAKES THE GRADE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
TULSA, Okla. 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
lon Jennings has had fame and fortune as a country singer. 
</P>
<P>
Now, with a high school equivalency diploma, he says he has the edge. 
</P>
<P>
Jennings, who dropped out in the 10th grade, passed the exam in December. 
</P>
<P>
"Going back to get your high school diploma isn't the answer to all your 
problems by any means, but I'll tell you what it is: It's a psychological 
advantage," he said. 
</P>
<P>
"It gives you that little bitty edge. It'll make you go through a door that you 
wouldn't have gone through if you didn't have it, because you knew that 
somebody on the other side of the door was educated." 
</P>
</TEXT>
